Class Course

  • java.lang.Object
    • Course
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class Course
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Represents a course in the system. A course can be enrolled by a limited number(course size) of students.

              Faculty faculty,

        Course constructor Creates a course with course name, faculty who teaches this course, information of lecture, tutorial, lab of this course.
        Parameters:
        name - name of this course
        faculty - a Faculty object which stores information of the faculty who teaches this course
        lecture - a Lecture object which stores information of lecture of this course
        tutorial - an array of all Tutorial object, each object stores information of a tutorial session of this course
        lab - an array of Lab object,each object stores information of a lab session of this course
        tutorialDic - a dictionary which stores all tutorials of this course
        labDic - a dictionary which stores all labs of this course

        public boolean isFull()
        Checks whether this course if full or not. Checking is done by individually checking whether lecture, labs and tutorials are full or not.
        Returns:
        A boolean value. true if the course if full (course is full if any of lecture, labs or tutorials are full), false if this course has vacancy
